	<TD CLASS="smalltext">12 October 2001, 04:54 GMT</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD CLASS="largetext"><B>Images are back!</B></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD><IMG SRC="images/shim.gif" HEIGHT="10"></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD CLASS="mediumtext"><P>A month or so ago we moved GuildMagic onto a new server. This had to be done as a matter of urgency since it was using too much bandwidth and crippling the other sites on the server it was on. In the process of moving over we had to accept that we wouldn't have some of the facilities we used to have when GuildMagic was on our own server. One of the casualties was our image upload facility. </P>
<P>Well I've railed against giving up that feature for far too long. At the suggestion of our wonderful GuildMagic activists on the <A class="" target=_blank href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/bguildmagic">chat board</A> I've changed the system so that now you can enter the URL of your picture if it's uploaded somewhere on the internet.</P>
<P>Character and awards pictures have both been updated to work the same way now. Character picture URLs and award picture URLs can be a maximum of 250 chars long. All character pictures and award pictures have been automatically updated to use the new system and they should all be working fine.</P>
<P>So all you have to do to set your character picture is go back and edit your character and enter the URL of your picture in the character image field on the form.&nbsp;We are still having some problems when updating characters and skills so if you get an error when you submit the form you may need to re-try until it works. We're aware of this problem and we have a plan in place to fix it.</P>
<P>Regards,<BR>Lusanne</P></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD><IMG SRC="images/shim.gif" HEIGHT="10"></TD>
